text: Tengiz Sichinava (15 May 1972 â€“ 4 March 2021) was a Georgian football player and manager. He played as a midfielder. Sichinava left Georgia in 2001 for Russian First Division side Baltika Kaliningrad. In 2005, he left Georgia again for Azerbaijan side Turan Tovuz. He played for MKT Araz. Sichinava made his Georgia national team debut on 4 September 1999. He made ten appearances for them and left in 2000. ==References== Category:1972 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Footballers in Georgia (country) Category:Football managers
